Unfortunately, there are cases where nicknames are truly nicknames, not
merely shortened aliases.  CSNET formerly had four hosts allocated for
various support tasks; we merged four of the tasks into two machines and
gave them, as nicknames, the hostnames of the machines whose functions had
been absorbed (csnet-cic into csnet-sh, rand-relay into csnet-relay).  True,
we are trying to convince the alternate names to wither and die, but we
still get mail addressed to "csnet-cic@csnet-cic.arpa" when it hasn't had an
independent life of its own for well over a year.  Similarly, there are lots
of databases out there who know the name "rand-relay", and some people who
are sending out their own return addresses still specify
"name%csnet-host@rand-relay" (we scold the senders when we see this, but we
don't (must not!) look at all the mail that we handle).

Having nicknames available greatly smoothed a rough transition.

Dennis Rockwell
CSNET Technical Staff

